p: The highest rate of mild to moderate influenza disease (MMID) was observed in the placebo group, with 54.8% of participants experiencing MMID. In the two-dose FLU-v group, 36.6% ( p = 0.075) experienced MMID while 32.5% ( p = 0.035) experienced MMID in the one-dose FLU-v group, a statistically significant reduction in the primary endpoint vs the placebo group (Table 2).
